The public broadcaster says he was followed home from Auckland Park last night and shot at, but wasn't harmed. JOHANNESBURG - The SABC says a suspect has been arrested, following an alleged assassination attempt on its audit executive Thami Zikode. The public broadcaster says he was followed home from Auckland Park last night and shot at, but wasn't harmed. READ: SABC's audit executive survives 'attempted hit': reports The motive for the attack is not yet known, but it’s understood Zikode may have ruffled some feathers. He's currently working on a forensic investigation into fraud at the cash-strapped broadcaster. SABC spokesperson, Vuyo Mthembu, was on eNCA earlier.